== no target is required:
shit: 1:1: error: kill: Not enough arguments.
     1 |  kill
       |  ^~~~ here.
shit: note: Try `kill --help` for more info.
rc=2
== an unknown signal name is rejected:
shit: 1:1: error: Builtin 'kill': 'BOGUSSIG' is not a valid signal.
     1 |  kill -BOGUSSIG 123
       |  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
rc=1
== an unknown job is reported:
shit: 1:1: error: Builtin 'kill': '%999' is not a known job.
     1 |  kill %999
       |  ^~~~~~~~~ here.
rc=1
== a non-numeric job is rejected:
shit: 1:1: error: Builtin 'kill': '%abc' is not a known job.
     1 |  kill %abc
       |  ^~~~~~~~~ here.
rc=1
== a non-numeric pid is rejected:
shit: 1:1: error: Builtin 'kill': 'notanumber' is not a valid job or process id.
     1 |  kill notanumber
       |  ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
rc=1
